{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/oudstokenssemantic\/multipleelevationcompositerawtoken"]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleElevationCompositeRawToken"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Semantic tokens which will wrap a combination of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ElevationCompositeRawToken"},{"type":"text","text":" depending to color scheme (i.e. light mode or dark mode)"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Kind of composite token with multiple values, but not named “composite” because this word is already used in the design system."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Allows to gather the multiple-value tokens from "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Figma"}]},{"type":"text","text":" inside one object."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"If an elevation token exists with its value depending to the color scheme, it must be packed in such ``MultipleElevationCompositeRawToken`"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"final","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MultipleElevationCompositeRawToken","kind":"identifier"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["        \/\/ Assuming in Figma with have a elevation semantic token none,","        \/\/ with values depending to color scheme. These values are defined as elevation raw tokens.","        let bottom_0 = ElevationCompositeRawToken(x: x0, y: y0, blur: blur0, color: ColorRawTokens.opacityBlack0)","        let bottom_1_100 = ElevationCompositeRawToken(x: x0, y: y100, blur: blur200, color: ColorRawTokens.opacityBlack100)","","        \/\/ Then the develoment team declares an \"higher\" level elevation semantic token","        \/\/ inside ElevationCompositeSemanticTokens protocol,","        \/\/ and defined inside OrangeTheme+ElevationCompositeSemanticTokens extension","        \/\/ ElevationCompositeSemanticToken is a typealias for MultipleElevationCompositeRawToken to keep same grammar as design kit","        var none: ElevationCompositeSemanticToken {","            ElevationCompositeSemanticToken(light: bottom_0, dark: bottom_1_100)","        }","","        \/\/ If the same elevation is used whatever the color scheme is","        var none: ElevationCompositeSemanticToken {","            ElevationCompositeSemanticToken(bottom_0)","        }"]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["        \/\/ The theme exposes both generated elevation semantic tokens and \"crafted\" higher level elevation semantic tokens.","        \/\/ It is recommended to use the higher level version as it is less error-prone.","","        @Environment(\\.theme) var theme","        @Environment(\\.colorScheme) var colorScheme","","        \/\/ Given you want to apply the elevation token \"raised\"","        var body: some View {","            \/\/ Apply the token of elevation for the shadow effect without managing yourself the color scheme","            Rectangle()","                .shadow(elevation: theme.elevations.raised))","        }"]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["    \/\/ Or get the token depending to the color scheme and do whatever you want with","    theme.elevations.raised.elevation(for: colorScheme)"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The case of this "},{"code":"MultipleElevationCompositeRawToken","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is quite particular because in fact it contains "},{"code":"MultipleElevationCompositeRawToken","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" (i.e. raw tokens) instead of semantic tokens."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"In fact only the "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"color"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" of the elevation effect vary depending to the color scheme,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"but in the "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Figma"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" kit this is composite raw tokens which are defined for ligh and dark mode as only one token."}]},{"type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"0.8.0"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Since","style":"note"}],"kind":"content"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic"]]},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Class","externalID":"c:@M@OUDSTokensSemantic@objc(cs)MultipleElevationCompositeRawToken","title":"MultipleElevationCompositeRawToken","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"MultipleElevationCompositeRawToken","kind":"identifier"}],"symbolKind":"class","role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"Tokens for semantics"}],"fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MultipleElevationCompositeRawToken","kind":"identifier"}]},"sections":[],"relationshipsSections":[{"title":"Inherits From","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/objc(cs)NSObject"],"type":"inheritsFrom","kind":"relationships"},{"title":"Conforms To","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/objc(pl)NSObject","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/s7CVarArgP","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/s28CustomDebugStringConvertibleP","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/s23CustomStringConvertibleP","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/SQ","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/SH","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/s8SendableP","doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/s16SendableMetatypeP"],"type":"conformsTo","kind":"relationships"}],"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"topicSections":[{"title":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleElevationCompositeRawToken\/init(_:)","doc:\/\/OUDST